name: Partition
description: Base class of Cache.OrgPartition and Cache.SessionPartition. Use the subclasses to manage the cache partition for org caches and session caches.

contains(string).name: contains
contains(string).description: Returns true if the cache partition contains a cached value corresponding to the specified key.

key.name: key
key.description: A case-sensitive string value that uniquely identifies a cached value.

createfullyqualifiedkey(string,string,st.name: createFullyQualifiedKey
createfullyqualifiedkey(string,string,st.signature: public static String createFullyQualifiedKey(String namespace, String partition, String key)
createfullyqualifiedkey(string,string,st.overrideSignature: public static override String createFullyQualifiedKey(String namespace, String partition, String key)
createfullyqualifiedkey(string,string,st.description: Generates a fully qualified key from the passed-in key components. The format of the generated key string is namespace.partition.key.

key.name: key
key.description: The namespace of the cache key. The partition of the cache key. The name of the cache key.

createfullyqualifiedpartition(string,str.name: createFullyQualifiedPartition
createfullyqualifiedpartition(string,str.signature: public static String createFullyQualifiedPartition(String namespace, String partition)
createfullyqualifiedpartition(string,str.overrideSignature: public static override String createFullyQualifiedPartition(String namespace, String partition)
createfullyqualifiedpartition(string,str.description: Generates a fully qualified partition name from the passed-in namespace and partition. The format of the generated partition string is namespace.partition.

partition.name: partition
partition.description: The namespace of the cache key. The partition of the cache key.

get(string).name: get
get(string).description: Returns the cached value corresponding to the specified key from the cache partition.

key.name: key
key.description: A case-sensitive string value that uniquely identifies a cached value.

get(system.type,string).name: get
get(system.type,string).signature: public Object get(System.Type cacheBuilder, String key)
get(system.type,string).overrideSignature: public override Object get(System.Type cacheBuilder, String key)
get(system.type,string).description: Returns the cached value corresponding to the specified key from the partition cache. Use this method if your cached value is a class that implements the CacheBuilder interface.

key.name: key
key.description: The Apex class that implements the CacheBuilder interface. A case-sensitive string value that, combined with the class name corresponding to the cacheBuilder parameter, uniquely identifies a cached value.

getavggettime().name: getAvgGetTime
getavggettime().description: Returns the average time taken to get a key from the partition, in nanoseconds.

getavgvaluesize().name: getAvgValueSize
getavgvaluesize().description: Returns the average item size for keys in the partition, in bytes.

getcapacity().name: getCapacity
getcapacity().description: Returns the percentage of cache used of the total capacity for this partition.

getkeys().name: getKeys
getkeys().description: Returns a set of all keys that are stored in the cache partition and visible to the invoking namespace.

getmaxgettime().name: getMaxGetTime
getmaxgettime().description: Returns the maximum time taken to get a key from the partition, in nanoseconds.

getmaxvaluesize().name: getMaxValueSize
getmaxvaluesize().description: Returns the maximum item size for keys in the partition, in bytes.

getmissrate().name: getMissRate
getmissrate().description: Returns the miss rate in the partition.

getname().name: getName
getname().description: Returns the name of this cache partition.

getnumkeys().name: getNumKeys
getnumkeys().description: Returns the total number of keys in the partition.

isavailable().name: isAvailable
isavailable().description: Returns true if the Salesforce session is available. Only applies to Cache.SessionPartition. The session cache isnt available when an active session isnt present, such as in asynchronous Apex or code called by asynchronous Apex. For example, if batch Apex causes an Apex trigger to execute, the session cache isnt available in the trigger because the trigger runs in asynchronous context.

put(string,object).name: put
put(string,object).signature: public void put(String key, Object value)
put(string,object).overrideSignature: public override void put(String key, Object value)
put(string,object).description: Stores the specified key/value pair as a cached entry in the cache partition. The put method can write only to the cache in your orgs namespace.

value.name: value
value.description: A case-sensitive string value that uniquely identifies a cached value. The value to store in the cache. The cached value must be serializable.

put(string,object,cache.visibility).name: put
put(string,object,cache.visibility).signature: public void put(String key, Object value, cache.Visibility visibility)
put(string,object,cache.visibility).overrideSignature: public override void put(String key, Object value, cache.Visibility visibility)
put(string,object,cache.visibility).description: Stores the specified key/value pair as a cached entry in the cache partition and sets the cached values visibility.

visibility.name: visibility
visibility.description: A case-sensitive string value that uniquely identifies a cached value. The value to store in the cache. The cached value must be serializable. Indicates whether the cached value is available only to Apex code that is executing in the same namespace or to Apex code executing from any namespace.

put(string,object,integer).name: put
put(string,object,integer).signature: public void put(String key, Object value, Integer ttlSecs)
put(string,object,integer).overrideSignature: public override void put(String key, Object value, Integer ttlSecs)
put(string,object,integer).description: Stores the specified key/value pair as a cached entry in the cache partition and sets the cached values lifetime.

ttlsecs.name: ttlSecs
ttlsecs.description: A case-sensitive string value that uniquely identifies a cached value. The value to store in the cache. The cached value must be serializable. The amount of time, in seconds, to keep the cached value in the cache.

put(string,object,integer,cache.visibili.name: put
put(string,object,integer,cache.visibili.signature: public void put(String key, Object value, Integer ttlSecs, cache.Visibility visibility, Boolean immutable)
put(string,object,integer,cache.visibili.overrideSignature: public override void put(String key, Object value, Integer ttlSecs, cache.Visibility visibility, Boolean immutable)
put(string,object,integer,cache.visibili.description: Stores the specified key/value pair as a cached entry in the cache partition. This method also sets the cached values lifetime, visibility, and whether it can be overwritten by another namespace.

immutable.name: immutable
immutable.description: A case-sensitive string value that uniquely identifies a cached value. The value to store in the cache. The cached value must be serializable. The amount of time, in seconds, to keep the cached value in the cache. Indicates whether the cached value is available only to Apex code that is executing in the same namespace or to Apex code executing from any namespace. Indicates whether the cached value can be overwritten by another namespace (false) or not (true).

remove(string).name: remove
remove(string).description: Deletes the cached value corresponding to the specified key from this cache partition.

key.name: key
key.description: A case-sensitive string value that uniquely identifies a cached value.

remove(system.type,string).name: remove
remove(system.type,string).signature: public Boolean remove(System.Type cacheBuilder, String key)
remove(system.type,string).overrideSignature: public override Boolean remove(System.Type cacheBuilder, String key)
remove(system.type,string).description: Deletes the cached value corresponding to the specified key from the partition cache. Use this method if your cached value is a class that implements the CacheBuilder interface.

key.name: key
key.description: The Apex class that implements the CacheBuilder interface. A case-sensitive string value that, combined with the class name corresponding to the cacheBuilder parameter, uniquely identifies a cached value.

validatecachebuilder(system.type).name: validateCacheBuilder
validatecachebuilder(system.type).overrideSignature: public static override void validateCacheBuilder(System.Type cacheBuilder)
validatecachebuilder(system.type).description: Validates that the specified class implements the CacheBuilder interface.

validatekey(boolean,string).name: validateKey
validatekey(boolean,string).signature: public static void validateKey(Boolean isDefault, String key)
validatekey(boolean,string).overrideSignature: public static override void validateKey(Boolean isDefault, String key)
validatekey(boolean,string).description: Validates a cache key. This method throws a Cache.InvalidParamException if the key is not valid. A valid key is not null and contains alphanumeric characters.

key.name: key
key.description: Set to true if the key references a default partition. Otherwise, set to false. The key to validate.

validatekeyvalue(boolean,string,object).name: validateKeyValue
validatekeyvalue(boolean,string,object).signature: public static void validateKeyValue(Boolean isDefault, String key, Object value)
validatekeyvalue(boolean,string,object).overrideSignature: public static override void validateKeyValue(Boolean isDefault, String key, Object value)
validatekeyvalue(boolean,string,object).description: Validates a cache key and ensures that the cache value is non-null. This method throws a Cache.InvalidParamException if the key or value is not valid. A valid key is not null and contains alphanumeric characters.

value.name: value
value.description: Set to true if the key references a default partition. Otherwise, set to false. The key to validate. The cache value to validate.

validatekeys(boolean,set<string>).name: validateKeys
validatekeys(boolean,set<string>).signature: public static void validateKeys(Boolean isDefault, Set<String> keys)
validatekeys(boolean,set<string>).overrideSignature: public static override void validateKeys(Boolean isDefault, Set<String> keys)
validatekeys(boolean,set<string>).description: Validates the specified cache keys. This method throws a Cache.InvalidParamException if the key is not valid. A valid key is not null and contains alphanumeric characters.

keys.name: keys
keys.description: Set to true if the key references a default partition. Otherwise, set to false. A set of key string values to validate.

validatepartitionname(string).name: validatePartitionName
validatepartitionname(string).overrideSignature: public static override void validatePartitionName(String name)
validatepartitionname(string).description: Validates the partition name  for example, that it is not null.

name.name: name
name.description: The name of the partition to validate.
